      "content": "i don't think telling my manager is a good idea. if they're actually managing a massive transition like this, they wouldn't want some clerk knowing the full scope of the play. it feels like the patterns i'm seeing are intentional, like the data is being steered toward a specific outcome that most people aren't ready for. do you ever think that large organizations intentionally silo information so that only a few people at the very top—and maybe a few unsuspecting people on the ground—actually see the full picture?",
